e of loot.  Players helped each other, knowing that one day they would need help in return and it was their fellow players that would provide it.<br>
<br>
Then the world began to change.  With each new expansion, new loot was found.  And with each new expansion, new boundaries were formed to define how much money was expected to buy what loot.  Soon it came to pass that only those who had the loot could get into the raids to get more loot.  Then the people who had the loot began using it to create a new generation of people that would never know the challenge of facing a train of angry fire beetles with only a rusty sword and a guild tunic.  And this new generation had no understanding of the simple things, like spending a month trying to get to level 30, or helping a guy that needs helping, or spending 6 months saving up to buy that shiny new Mithril Breastplate.  These people seem to be weaned on greed.  They show no wish to better the Everquest community.  Instead they tell fresh new characters looking for help to go away.<br>
<br>
I have spent my 3 years in EQ helping everyone I see, no matter what lvl they are or how much plat they have in the bank.  As a cleric I give buffs and rezzes free to those who ask, as a wizard I offer ports to those in need, and with my other chars, I am equally gracious.  I am one of the few character walking around that when I get a new piece of gear I give my old gear to some newbie out there that needs it.  And after spending my EQ life in this fashion, I can say that nothing personifies this rampant greed of people wanting to exploit their fellow players for their hard earned money than enchanters charging people for Koadic's endless Intellect.<br>
<br>
Now don't get me wrong, people go get paid for buff and I believe that they should, but in the form of donations.  When druis on my server started trying to charge people too much for ports I created a wizard to put them out of business offering ports for free.  Perhaps now it's time to start an enchanter.  Because when I see an enchanter making 10kpp a night from casting KEI, and turning away VERY rudely, anyone unable to pay this toll, I get angry.  I mean come on, it costs nothing to cast this spell, and the donations that people offer are more than enough to justify the time spent.  Because of this new spell, more and more high end enchanters have stopped raiding and stared sitting in Nexus fleecing the public.  This must stop.  Personally, I have created many characters, several casters, without the aid of KEI and from where I sit I will not be asking for it again.  I deplore this greedy new threat to the EQ community, and I will do everything in my power to help combat it.  I ask that any of you people of Norrath that feel as I do, please stand with me, in shunning these greedy, money hungry bastards that are corrupting our fair world of Norrath.  And I don't hold this just to enchanter, though they are the main culprit.  But to anyone that I see who is taking unfair advantage of the people of the world, beware, I keep track, and I know that me, my alts, and my friends will never be there to rez, buff, port, SoW, summon your corpse, help, or back you up.  In short, you are a pox upon Norrath and if you will not open your eyes to what you are doing, I will most assuredly shut you down.  And, there are enough people between me, my wife and a friend to keep a 60 chanter in Nexus giving out free KEI to do it 24/7.  So let's stop with the greed and remember that helping our fellow player is what make this game worth playing.  Also a dire warning to the rest of you that you may have heard before...What goes around comes around.<br>
<br>
Damerr Flinn<br>
Cleric of Tunare<br>
