<br>
And the end of this, when chanters are so greedy that they won't even give a KEI out on a raid that they are a part of, there's a problem.  And yes, this happened to me recently on a Kith raid that I organized to help the chanter's buddy on.  No, I get told that she only casts KEI on people that can afford her 100pp charge.  And that was after a 56 cleric rezzed an entire Naggy raid for free, for those of you that want to cleric bash.  I don't think I've ever seen a cleric make 10kpp on rezzes in 3 hours, and if I did, I'd be the first to slap the greedy prick.  No one has EVER been as miserly and greedy as the enchanter community with a NO REAGENT spell!  Come on, you guys make up Shaka's 30kpp or even the EXTREMELY inflated 60kpp in a matter of days.  Sounds to me like you're doing much better than the rest of us who will NEVER make up the cost of our upper end spells.  For a group of people who's response to me is &quot;Quit whining...stand in line and take up the arse like the other casters&quot;  You seem to be making a point of whining about that price you paid for this spell that has you banking in the dough.  Guess what, there'll be another expansion eventually, Verant love that money just as much as you do, and don't be surprised to find yourself on the arse end of the class balancing stick.  God willing the rumors of a KEI nerf I keep hearing are true.  So suck it up while you can, but remember, every class get their 5 minutes of fame, and when it's over everyone still remembers whether you acted with honor and integrity, or how you acted to take advantage of others.  Personally, I don't care whether I have or don't have KEI, a cleric is always taken over a chanter because at the end of the day, we save lives.  And to those chanters out there that want to spend your time fleecing the populace because taking meager donations have only made you a meager 25 thousand platinum, enjoy it while it lasts.  But remember, every dog has his day, and that doesn't just apply to druids =).<br>
<br>
Damerr Flinn<br>
Cleric of Tunare<br>
Lanys T'Vyl <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shakaaus>ShakaAus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#330000>(11/20/02 10:18:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You must be joking!!!</span><hr size=1> Sounds like someone whishes they had been an enchanter instead of a cleric.  My point on the 25k was that I did not even make back what I spent on the spell.  And I am sorry to let you in on this little secret : Everquest is not a universal philanthropic experiment.  I appreciate your opinion, and even empathize as I myself have often wondered why we dont do more sharing.  But the fact is I want to see and do places like Vex Thal and Hall of Honor.  And the fact is to do these places you need gear that rocks and to get to the places that drops the no drop gear that rocks you need to buy gear that will let you live in those places.  Get off your high horse buddy, oh wait, you cannot afford one.  Ummmm get off your soapbox and go enjoy the game for what it is... a microcosim of the real world.  If you want to roleplay a social worker.. Super <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , every community needs one. Be a guide or some other help intensive, thank you based reward character.  I cannot believe you would fault a character for taking advantage of their abilities - I can only assume you are insane with jealously.<br>
<br>
As far as casting KEI on a raid, well maybe your server is just filled with enchanters tired of dealing with sniveling little gimme whiners like yourself.  I myself do free KEI's for CR's, and of course if 'I' am on the raid I KEI the whole raid.  I am sure we are missing part of the story when it comes to your mysterious unKEIing ench.  <br>
<br>
Also, 900 mana is a damn big chunk of the mana pool.  So if you come across an enchanter in the field and he doesnt throw KEI on you just cuz dont be suprised, enchanters need that mana to keep groups alive. <br>
<br>
As far as clerics being better - - - - well every class is needed, no doubt.  But I have been in plenty of higher end groups and often have no cleric.  Not that I dont think they are needed, not bashing clerics or any other class so dont go running with that thread or I will just delete my post.  I am just amazed that you have played the game this long and are still crying. <br>
<br>
Also, my point on the 25k was only that I planned on taking donations till I recovered my 34k.  But, so many people refused to donate after i had cast that i just gave up on it altogether.  I made my character from scratch, and dont owe anyone jack, so dont tell me how i am obligated to dump kei on you just because it is componentless.  Gotta go now i feel my blueberry waffles coming back up.<br>
<br>
<br>
Shakamez 64 ench Bristlebane server. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=llyrofneriak>Llyr of Neriak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(11/20/02 12:38:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=236.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You must be joking!!!</span><hr size=1> I find it ironic that a person counseling a &quot;kinder, gentler Norrath&quot; (my paraphrase, not his), in the same rant resorts to threatening to make those that don't comply with his Utopia as uncomfortable as he can.  Can you say &quot;situational ethics&quot;?  I knew you could.<br>
<br>
